


What is the Decorator Design Pattern?
................................
The Decorator Pattern is a Structural Design Pattern used to add new functionality to an object dynamically without modifying its existing code.

Definition: The Decorator Pattern wraps an existing object with another object (decorator) to add new behavior while keeping the original class unchanged.

Real-Time Banking Example
................................
................................
Suppose a bank has a basic notification service.

Initially:

Transaction

↓

SMS Notification

Later, the business wants:

SMS
Email
WhatsApp

Instead of modifying the existing SMS class, we decorate it with additional features.

Notification

↓

SMS

↓

Email

↓

WhatsApp

Step 1: Component Interface
................................
public interface Notification {

    void send();
}

Step 2: Concrete Component
................................
public class SmsNotification implements Notification {

    @Override
    public void send() {

        System.out.println("SMS Notification Sent");
    }
}

Step 3: Decorator
................................
public abstract class NotificationDecorator
        implements Notification {

    protected Notification notification;

    public NotificationDecorator(Notification notification) {

        this.notification = notification;
    }
}

Step 4: Email Decorator
................................
public class EmailNotification
        extends NotificationDecorator {

    public EmailNotification(Notification notification) {

        super(notification);
    }

    @Override
    public void send() {

        notification.send();

        System.out.println("Email Notification Sent");
    }
}

Step 5: WhatsApp Decorator
................................
public class WhatsAppNotification
        extends NotificationDecorator {

    public WhatsAppNotification(Notification notification) {

        super(notification);
    }

    @Override
    public void send() {

        notification.send();

        System.out.println("WhatsApp Notification Sent");
    }
}

Step 6: Main Class
................................
public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Notification notification =
                new WhatsAppNotification(
                        new EmailNotification(
                                new SmsNotification()));

        notification.send();
    }
}

